<li>  Report of the President's Biomedical Research
Panel., Appendix A US Department of Health, Education and Welfare,
publication (OS) 76-50, p 19-21, 236.</FONT>
<P>
<li> Report of the panel on Chemicals and health
of the President's Science Advisory Committee.  Science and Technology
Policy Office, National Science Foundation, p 113. </FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Arial">3. In addition, certain other entities, such
as selected foreign drug regulatory authorities, will be recognized
as being able to certify that a product is safe and effective.</FONT>
<LI><FONT FACE="Arial">&quot;NDA&quot; is used here to include
PLAs as well; with the exception of blood products and similar
entities, such as tissue and sperm banks, the regulation of drugs
and biologics will be indistinguishable, and ELAs (Establishment
Licensing Applications) will be eliminated.</FONT>
<LI><FONT FACE="Arial">GLPs = Good Laboratory Practice Regulations;
GCPs = Good Clinical Practice Regulations; and GMPs = Good Manufacturing
Practice Regulations.</FONT>
</OL>

