<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<TITLE>Bibliography</TITLE>
<H2>Bibliography</H2>
<HR SIZE=2>


<P><I>Adjustment in Africa, Reforms, Results, and the Road Ahead,</I> A World Bank Policy 
Research Report, The World Bank, Washington, D.C., March, 1994.
<P><I>Asia and the Pacific: A Tax Tour,</I> Arthur Andersen & Co.,  New York, New York, 1993.
<P><I>Corporate Taxes: A Worldwide Summary,</I> Price Waterhouse, 1993 and 1994 editions, 
New York, 1993 and 1994.
<P><I>Country Reports on Economic Policy and Trade Practices</I>, report submitted to the 
Committee on Foreign relations, Committee on Finance, of the U.S. Senate, and the Committee 
on Foreign Affairs, Committee on Ways and Means, of the U.S. House of Representatives by the 
Department of State, February 1994.
<P><I>Country Reports on Human Rights Practices</I>, report submitted to the Committee on 
Foreign Affairs, U.S. House of Representatives, and the Committee on Foreign Relations, U.S., 
Senate by the Department of Defense, February 1994.
<P><I>Cuba: Handbook of Trade Statistics, 1994</I>, The Central Intelligence Agency, Washington, 
D.C., 1994.
<P>Delotte Touche Tohmatsu International, <I>International Tax and Business Reports</I>, various 
country specific reports, New York, 1993 to 1994.
<P><I>Doing Business In</I>, Information Guide on various countries, Price Waterhouse, New York, 
1993 to 1994
<P><I>Economic and Social Progress in Latin America: 1993 Report</I>, Inter-American 
Development Bank, Washington, D.C. 1993
<P>Economic Intelligence Unit, <I>Investment Trade and Licensing Reports</I>, various country 
specific reports, Washington, D.C., 1993-1994
