<P><I>Geographical Distribution of Financial Flows to Developing Countries: 1989/1992</I>.  The 
Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development, Paris, France, 1994.
<P><I>Global Survey 1993: Regulatory and Market Developments</I>, Institute of International 
Bankers, New York, New York, September 1993
<P><I>Government Finance Statistics Yearbook: 1993</I>, The International Monetary Fund, 
Washington, D.C., 1993
<P><I>Human Development Report: 1993</I>, United Nations Development Project, United Nations, 
New York, 1993.
<P><I>Individual Taxes: A Worldwide Summary</I>, Price Waterhouse, 1993 and 1994 editions, New 
York, 1993 and 1994.
<P><I>International Financial Statistics</I>, The International Monetary Fund, Washington, D.C., 
1994
<P><I>International Trade Statistics</I>, The International Monetary Fund, Washington, D.C., 1994
KPMG Peat Marwick, various country guides, Washington, D.C. 1993 to 1994
<P>Lau, Lawrence J., <I>Models of Development: A Comparative Study of Economic Growth in 
South Korea and Taiwan</I>, International Center for Economic Growth, ICS Press, San 
Francisco, 1990
<P>Larroulet, Cristian V., ed., <I>Private Solutions to Public Problems: The Chilean Experience</I>, 
Instituto Libertad Y Desarrollo, Trieno S.A., Chile, 1991 
<P>Naya, Seiji and Robert McCleery, <I>Relevance of Asian Development Experiences to African 
Problems</I>, International Center for Economic Growth, ICS Press San Francisco, California, 
1994
<P>McCormick, Shawn H., <I>The Angolan Economy: Prospect for Growth in a Postwar 
Environment</I>,  Center for Strategic and International Studies, Washington, D.C., 1994

<P>Shepard, Geoffrey, and Langoni, Carlos Geraldo, eds., <I>Trade Reform: Lessons From Eight 
Countries</I>, International Center for Economic Growth, ICS Press, San Francisco, 1991
