<html><head><title>Medicare Survey Results</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg"><h2><center>Medicare Survey Results</center></h2><hr>
<P>
<b>Question:</b> Do you believe "Medicare Reform" is an important issue for Congress to address?<P>Increase: 100%<br>Decrease: 0%

<P><b>Question:</b> Do you believe the Republican or the Democrats are more sincere about reforming Medicare?<P>Republicans: 83%<br>Democrats: 17%

<p><b>Question</b>Should seniors be allowed to opt out of Medicare for private insurance?<P>Yes: 75:<br>No: 25%

<p><b>Question</b> The Democrats claim that the money saved by refoming Medicare is being used to fund a tax break for the wealthy. Do you believe them?<p>Yes: 17%<br>No: 83%

<P><b>Question</b> Are you concerned that the Medicare system will not be solvent when it is your turn to receive benefits?<P>Yes: 84%<br>No: 16%

<p><b>Question</b> If Medicare reform does not pass this year, who will you hold responsible?<P>Republicans: 88%<br>No: 12%



